Malaysia Stocks: EP Manufacturing, Pensonic, SEG International

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-04-29T09:19:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/malaysia-stocks-ep-manufacturing-pensonic-seg-international.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in Kuala
Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index was little changed at
1,534.95. The gauge gained 0.8 percent this week and is down 0.7
percent for the month. The market will be shut on May 2 for a
public holiday.        EP Manufacturing Bhd. (EPMB)  , an auto-parts maker,
advanced 2.6 percent to 78.5 sen, its highest close since March
2005, after first-quarter net income doubled from a year earlier
to 8.6 million ringgit ($2.9 million).        Gadang Holdings Bhd. (GADG)  , a property and construction
group, dropped 1.4 percent to 69 sen. Net income in the third
quarter ended Feb. 28 declined 48 percent from a year earlier to
2.32 million ringgit, according to a company statement.  Pensonic Holdings Bhd. (PSN)  , an electronic and
electrical home appliances maker, rose 1.5 percent to 69 sen,
the most since April 18. Pensonicâ€™s profit in the third quarter
ended Feb. 28 more than doubled from a year earlier to 896,000
ringgit as sales climbed, according to a stock exchange
statement.        SEG International Bhd. (SYS)  , a college operator,
climbed 2 percent to a record 4.05 ringgit. First-quarter net
income surged 91 percent from a year earlier to 18.1 million
ringgit as sales rose, according to a company statement. SEG
also plans to split each of its shares into two, it said in a
separate statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
